"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oQuCy8nfCq0?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> “You can see it, you can climb it, you can parkour it,” explained Votypka of the historical open map environments.</p><p> Players will be able to grab onto lifts to pull themselves onto rooftops and then grab the virtual handholds and footholds that form the foundation of the fluid parkour.</p><p> However, if that isn&#39;t the player&#39;s preference, there is an auto-parkour setting which automatically takes the player to wherever they are looking. A “fear of heights” feature also fixes a grid to the players feet to prevent them from feeling like they really are on top of a roof.</p><p> Regarding stealth, Red Storm Entertainment has taken an action-oriented approach. Players will have to grab onto walls to lean their Assassin out to assess situations and “dynamic objects” can be picked up and thrown to distract enemies.</p><p> <em>Assassin&#39;s Creed Nexus VR</em> will also allow players to whistle to get a guard&#39;s attention by registering the action of forming a circle with their index finger and thumb and bringing it to their face. </p><figure id="attachment_3518676" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3518676" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-3518676 size-full" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2.jpg" alt="'Assassin’s Creed Nexus VR' Credit: Ubisoft" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-stealth-and-parkour-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3518676" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Assassin&#39;s Creed Nexus VR&#39; Credit: Ubisoft</figcaption></figure><p> As for combat, the player&#39;s arsenal will include smoke bombs, throwing knives and the Hidden Blade, which will be triggered by pressing a button on the controller and then flicking the wrist.</p><p> Ezio, Connor and Kassandra all have access to a ranged weapon to pick enemies off from afar, and the hand-to-hand combat encounters will require the player to slash and block with their controllers.</p><p> <em>Assassin&#39;s Creed Nexus VR</em> comes to Meta Quest 2, 3 and Pro on November 16.</p><p> In other gaming news, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/diablo-4-is-free-to-play-this-weekend-on-xboxdiablo-4-is-free-to-play-this-weekend-3518541"><em>Diablo 4</em> is free to play for all Xbox players between October 19 and 22</a> , alongside <em>Hokko Life, Lawn Mowing Simulator</em> and <em>NBA 2K24</em> for Xbox Game Pass subscribers.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/assassins-creed-nexus-vr-shows-off-parkour-and-stealth-in-new-deep-dive-3518663">&#39;Assassin&#39;s Creed Nexus VR&#39; shows off parkour and stealth in new deep dive</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
